<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Workshop Coordinator</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Workshop Coordinator<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Julie Hertzog<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, Exempt
</p>


<h3>RESPONSIBILITIES</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Coordinate all aspects of scheduling workshops. Including, but not limited to:
		<ul>
			<li>Scheduling the date, time and location of workshop site</li>
			<li>Order appropriate AV equipment</li>
			<li>Arrange for food and beverage </li>
			<li>Manage all invoicing for workshop sites, printing and mailing</li>
			<li>Manage all lodging requests</li>
			<li>Design and create workshop flyers</li>
			<li>Coordinating the printing of flyers/notices &#8211; Working with printer representatives</li>
			<li>Coordinating the mail list &#8211; Working with mail house representative</li>
			<li>Provide advocates and front office staff with all workshop information</li>
			<li>Create PDF for all materials</li>
			<li>Ensure all information is posted to the website (working with web manager)</li>
			<li>Create reminder postcards for all participants</li>
			<li>Schedule sign language interpreters when requested and handle payments to interpreters</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Manage PCIS database for all  workshop information</li>
	<li>Assist with alternate  methods to promote workshops</li>
	<li>Manage the scheduling of all  in house workshops and large conference room activities</li>
	<li>Manage the PACER Conference  Room calendar</li>
	<li>Execute administrative duties as required by various projects.</li>
	<li>&nbsp;Coordination of larger  conferences/events when necessary. Including logistics, registration, food, AV,  onsite staff coordination, etc.</li>
	<li>Other duties as necessary</li>
</ol>

<h3>REQUIREMENTS</h3>
<ul>
	<li>College degree preferred </li>
	<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
	<li>Accuracy and attention to detail necessary</li>
	<li>Strong organizational skills</li>
	<li>Strong  ability to multitask</li>
	<li>Ability to prioritize and complete time sensitive projects</li>
	<li>Ability to work independently and participate in team planning</li>
	<li>Knowledge of/sensitivity to issues related to persons with disabilities</li>
	<li>Knowledge of Microsoft Word</li>
	<li>Design software (In Design, PC) knowledge preferred, but not required</li>
</ul>


<p>
Parents of children and young adults with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
Salary will be based on experience and qualifications.
</p>
<p>Submit  resume with cover letter to:<br />
	Human Resources | PACER Center | 8161    Normandale Boulevard | Minneapolis, MN 55437</p>
